summary: PRE-REC // dublab presents – The Sounds of Now
description: The Sounds of Now is a program featuring a selection of new music and recent re-issues. With weekly updates The Sounds of Now offers listeners the opportunity to stay up to date on what is being released across the wide musical landscape from around the world. You can tune in to The Sounds of Now on dublab radio during the afterhours of our live broadcast, or subscribe to our weekly selections of new music on Spotify, Facebook and our Youtube channel.

Two-Step Verification exists as another entry into the world of Swami Sound’s making. The show’s title was inspired by a tweet; which in turn began a mix series on Soundcloud; and further evolved into a curated playlist and rave series of the same name: all helped along by the artist’s addiction to the Internet. Swami enters 2023 with the ideal setting for his online brainbaby as a monthly radio slot on dublab. It’s a looksee of Swami Sound’s foray into the UK Garage/Two Step Genre with a scope turned on Internet discovery. The show engages the dance music community in whatever online niche Swami finds them in. His audience has widened as a result of consistently posting his mixes and music — whether it’s through the unique sound or sultry IDs that his crowds request persistently at his shows. With guest mixes, sound bites, and interviews by collaborators, curators, inspirations and the sort, Swami injects dublab’s feed with the very syncopated rhythms that have uploaded his musical career into a new realm while joyfully engaging with the people over the tempos of the Web.

summary: PRE-REC // LARAAJI LAUGHS ~ a laughter meditation
description:
Every Thursday, Laraaji energizes the dublab airwaves with three minutes of luminous laughter flowing on celestial music beds on LARAAJI LAUGHS. Tune-in and smile as he centers us in a space of transformative joy!

The visionary musician and practitioner of Seriously Playful Laughter Meditation Workshops knows that jubilant eruptions do the body, mind, and soul good. You can read some of his insights into the physiological benefits of a nice, deep laugh here.

Laraaji hopes these offerings encourage you to play with your own laughter, sending the medicinal sounds into your head, chest, and abdomen.

“LAUGHTER IS THE BEST MEDICINE ~ LIGHTEN UP, LOOSEN UP, LAUGH IT UP.” - Laraaji

summary: PRE-REC // Out There ~ a field recording program
description: Voyage with dublab into new worlds. Each week we present a long-form field recording that will transport you through the power of sound. Tune-in, open up, and venture out there as we take excursions into evocative audio fields together.
Dying Songs focuses on new electronic music, usually the more experimental, dreamy, ghostly, pretty, sad side. Also occasional looks back or into other musical worlds.

summary: LIVE // Daddy Differently & Dirty Dave – Things of Life
description: It’s the simple things isn’t it? The little things of life. Good food, sunshine, no traffic, dark coffee, 72˚ breeze, telephone off the hook and music every Friday morning a la Daddy Differently.
